        <h3>Image Quality & Sensor Performance</h3>
        <p>
          The 45-megapixel stacked CMOS sensor delivers exceptional image quality with Canon's renowned color science. Resolution is sufficient for large commercial prints while maintaining excellent high-ISO performance. Dynamic range measures approximately 14+ stops at base ISO, providing significant latitude for exposure adjustments. The stacked architecture enables faster readout with minimal rolling shutter artifacts.
        </p>
        <p>
          High-ISO performance is impressiveâ€”ISO 6400 produces clean, usable images with excellent color retention, and ISO 12800 remains highly usable for event and wedding work. Canon's color rendition is particularly pleasing for skin tones, often requiring minimal post-processing. The 14-bit RAW files preserve subtle gradations and respond beautifully to editing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Eye Control AF System</h3>
        <p>
          The R5 II's headline feature is Eye Control AFâ€”after a 60-second calibration, you literally look at a subject and the camera focuses there. This is dramatically faster than joystick or touchscreen AF point selection, particularly valuable for action photography. The Dual Pixel CMOS AF II system features 1,053 AF zones covering 100% of the frame horizontally and vertically.
        </p>
        <p>
          Subject detection recognizes people (face/eye/body), animals (dogs, cats, birds, horses), and vehicles (motorsports, aircraft, trains). Tracking success rate exceeds 95% in real-world testing. Low-light AF works reliably down to -6.5 EV with f/1.2 lenses. The combination of Eye Control AF, deep learning tracking, and comprehensive subject detection creates the most intuitive focusing experience available.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Video Capabilities</h3>
        <p>
          The R5 II builds on its predecessor's video prowess. Internal 8K 60p RAW recording uses the full sensor width, delivering exceptional detail for professional productions. 4K 120p is available without crop for high-quality slow motion. Cinema RAW Light and Canon Log 3 provide approximately 15 stops of dynamic range for professional color grading workflows.
        </p>
        <p>
          Heat management is significantly improved over the original R5. Continuous 8K 30p recording is possible for approximately 30 minutes, while 4K 60p can record for 90+ minutes without overheating. The vari-angle touchscreen is invaluable for video work, and focus breathing compensation works with supported RF lenses. Full-size HDMI enables external RAW recording for ultimate flexibility.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Ergonomics & Build</h3>
